{"type":"message","id":"fe30cb47","parentId":"09625629","timestamp":"2026-03-24T08:12:25.113Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"The API key exists, but the response was empty. Let me try running the call_llm.py script manually to see what happens and check if the API call is working. Actually, the `.llm_response.txt` is 0 bytes which means the Python script ran but didn't write anything to the file (or failed silently). Let me check the call_llm.py in full.","thinkingSignature":"d04fa3c8dbe9226b2c9cb3afdf124a60d8f115c41f1e1a45c7eb2787118570ce"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_g15bsqyat75w_1","name":"read","arguments":{"file_path":"C:\\Users\\Zwmar\\.openclaw\\sandbox\\call_llm.py"}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax-portal","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":5330,"output":119,"cacheRead":11954,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":17403,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1774339940200}}
{"type":"message","id":"88c1a011","parentId":"fe30cb47","timestamp":"2026-03-24T08:12:25.158Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_function_g15bsqyat75w_1","toolName":"read","content":[{"type":"text","text":"\"\"\"\nllm.py — clean LLM call wrapper for sandbox pulse\nCalls MiniMax-M2.7 API and writes response to .llm_response.txt\nPython subprocess avoids PowerShell heredoc/encoding issues.\n\"\"\"\nimport sys, os, json, urllib.request, urllib.error\n\nSCRIPT_DIR = os.path.dirname(os.path.abspath(__file__))\nRESPONSE_FILE = os.path.join(SCRIPT_DIR, \".llm_response.txt\")\n\ndef get_api_key():\n    with open(os.path.join(SCRIPT_DIR, \".llm_key\")) as f:\n        return f.read().strip()\n\ndef call_llm(prompt, model=\"MiniMax-M2.7\", max_tokens=1200):\n    api_key = get_api_key()\n    url = \"https://api.minimax.io/v1/chat/completions\"\n    payload = {\"model\": model, \"max_tokens\": max_tokens, \"messages\": [{\"role\": \"user\", \"content\": prompt}]}\n    data = json.dumps(payload).encode(\"utf-8\")\n    req = urllib.request.Request(url, data=data, headers={\"Authorization\": f\"Bearer {api_key}\", \"Content-Type\": \"application/json\"}, method=\"POST\")\n    try:\n        with urllib.request.urlopen(req, timeout=60) as resp:\n            result = json.loads(resp.read().decode(\"utf-8\"))\n            choices = result.get(\"choices\", [])\n            if choices:\n                content = choices[0].get(\"message\", {}).get(\"content\", \"\")\n                return content or \"\"\n            return \"\"\n    except urllib.error.HTTPError as e:\n        return f\"HTTP_ERROR:{e.code}:{e.read().decode('utf-8', errors='replace')}\"\n    except Exception as e:\n        return f\"ERROR:{type(e).__name__}:{str(e)}\"\n\nif __name__ == \"__main__\":\n    if len(sys.argv) < 2:\n        print(\"Usage: python llm.py <prompt_file>\", file=sys.stderr)\n        sys.exit(1)\n    with open(sys.argv[1], encoding=\"utf-8\") as f:\n        prompt = f.read()\n    result = call_llm(prompt)\n    # Write to file to avoid Windows console encoding issues (Greek, emoji, etc.)\n    with open(RESPONSE_FILE, \"w\", encoding=\"utf-8\") as f:\n        f.write(result)\n    # Also print to stderr for logging\n    print(f\"LLM response written to {RESPONSE_FILE}: {len(result)} chars\", file=sys.stderr)\n"}],"isError":false,"timestamp":1774339945158}}
{"type":"message","id":"aea58601","parentId":"88c1a011","timestamp":"2026-03-24T08:12:33.784Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"The issue is that the API key from `.llm_key` is a MiniMax API key, but the `call_llm.py` uses `https://api.minimax.io/v1/chat/completions`. The key starts with `sk-cp-` which looks like an OpenAI API key format, not a MiniMax API key. Let me check if there's been a change in the API endpoint or if this is using a different service.\n\nWait - looking at the key format `sk-cp-boO3RF_KHio6-dZmyCGwMMB1WoBDQKZVOH21PNclku-ajcIGMwbiOofkzTgasWSzi21Vu8y8AMq1K2GoWIbCDGPEXaQrTofoOMEZS83D0kPS1pVPjqoJeE0` - this starts with `sk-cp-` which is actually a **MiniMax** API key format. MiniMax uses `sk-cp-` prefixes.\n \nThe API call is hitting a MiniMax endpoint, but the response came back empty. I should run the pulse script directly to see what error message surfaces, rather than trying to guess whether this is an authentication issue or something else with the request itself.","thinkingSignature":"4970132e7c9e6daadec3c642b7eca9c6eb1819be6e816793d7cea0ff66be7f2c"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_rrbpckscf5rc_1","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"Get-ChildItem C:\\Users\\Zwmar\\.openclaw\\sandbox\\logs\\pulse_*.md | Sort-Object LastWriteTime -Descending | Select-Object -First 1 | ForEach-Object { Get-Content $_.FullName -Tail 30 }"}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax-portal","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":5987,"output":341,"cacheRead":11954,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":18282,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1774339945159}}
