riants\r\n- Validate against success criteria (>70%, >60%)\r\n\r\nSo I should start working on the TIC experiment. The most concrete first step would be to create a script that analyzes the existing pulse logs to classify content as invariant vs variant."}],"details":{"status":"completed","exitCode":0,"durationMs":591,"aggregated":"=== pulse_2026-03-24 030316.md ===\r\n# Pulse: 2026-03-24 030316\r\n\r\n## Applied Mutations\r\nNo mutations applied this cycle.\r\nRejected: the (missing)\r\n\r\n## LLM Response\r\n<think>\r\nLet me review the current state and determine what single concrete action to take.\r\n\r\nLooking at the goals:\r\n1. Phase 0 and Phase 1 are marked COMPLETE\r\n2. The key pending action is the TIC Experiment (Temporal Invariance Compression)\r\n3. Success criteria: >70% invariant/variant classification, >60% next-pulse prediction\r\n4. Need to implement TIC classifier on `logs/pulse_*.md` files\r\n\r\nThe most concrete next step would be to implement the TIC classifier or create a document outlining the experiment setup. Given the instruction to prefer file edits, I should create or modify a file.\r\n\r\nLet me check what's in the logs directory to understand the pulse log format, then create a TIC implementation.\r\n\r\nActually, let me first check what files exist in the sandbox to understand the current state better.\r\n</think>\r\n\r\nLooking at the goals, the most concrete next action is implementing the TIC (Temporal Invariance Compression) classifier on the pulse logs. Let me first examine the existing pulse logs to understand their format.\r\n<minimax:tool_call>\r\n<invoke name=\"ls\">\r\n<parameter name=\"parameters\">{\"path\": \"logs\"}</parameter>\r\n</invoke>\r\n</minimax:tool_call>\r\n\r\n\r\n=== pulse_2026-03-24 030013.md ===\r\n# Pulse: 2026-03-24 030013\r\n\r\n## Applied Mutations\r\nNo mutations applied this cycle.\r\nRejected: tic/tic-classifier.ps1 (missing)\r\n\r\n## LLM Response\r\n<think>\r\nLet me review the current state:\r\n\r\n1. The goals document shows Phase 0 and Phase 1 as complete\r\n2. The key pending action is the TIC (Temporal Invariance Compression) Experiment\r\n3. Success criteria: >70% invariant/variant classification, >60% next-pulse prediction\r\n4. Need to implement TIC classifier on `logs/pulse_*.md` files\r\n\r\nLooking at the logs directory, there are several pulse logs. The next action should be implementing the TIC classifier.\r\n\r\nLet me check what files exist and what needs to be done for the TIC experiment.\r\n\r\nFrom the goals:\r\n- [ ] Implement TIC classifier on `logs/pulse_*.md` files\r\n- [ ] Measure invariant/variant classification accuracy\r\n- [ ] Predict next pulse content from invariants\r\n- [ ] Validate against success criteria (>70%, >60%)\r\n\r\nThe immediate next action should be creating a TIC classifier. This is a concrete file edit/create action.\r\n\r\nI should create a script that:\r\n1. Reads pulse logs\r\n2. Identifies invariant (stable across pulses) vs variant (changing) content\r\n\r\n=== pulse_2026-03-24 025914.md ===\r\n# Pulse: 2026-03-24 025914\r\n\r\n## Applied Mutations\r\nNo mutations applied this cycle.\r\n\r\n\r\n## LLM Response\r\n<think>\r\nLet me review the context and determine what single concrete action I should take.\r\n\r\nCurrent state:\r\n- Phase 0 COMPLETE: Sandbox foundation established\r\n- Phase 1 COMPLETE: Architecture cross-analysis + integration spec synthesized\r\n- Major insights developed this session about gap-decay synthesis and compression-causal duality\r\n- NEXT ACTION is to implement TIC (Temporal Invariance Compression) classifier on pulse logs\r\n\r\nThe pending tasks include:\r\n- Write PowerShell wrapper for FocusDecayMemory CLI\r\n- Define significance scoring for pulse content\r\n- Tune ? empirically\r\n- Wire Breakaway pulses to real TemporalAttention backend\r\n- Measure compression ratio\r\n\r\nThe immediate next action from Phase 1 Advancement is:\r\n- Implement TIC classifier on `logs/pu